🎶🎶🎶 Next song release!!!!!! Album cover final slide! Coming to you end of April 💕

This song was hard. This song hurt. I had to touch unhealed wounds to record this song. Divorce (breakups too), is extremely hard. Especially when you love someone who is constantly lying, manipulating and hurting you. Leaving was scary: “I tried all I could.”

I found my strength when I left him. Healing from narcissism abuse isn’t easy but I found my voice, my own badass self and most of all my independence. I hope this song helps those who are in a relationship they know they shouldn’t be in and gives you courage to leave. You deserve to be happy and you deserve to be YOU 🙌

What Did I Do? ⛔️

Being with someone who doesn’t value you, can really mess with your head. It can really reshape the way you think. Being cheating on, freaking sucks. Being married to someone who cheated on me with multiple different woman, was horrible and I lost myself. I started to look within and think…
- what did I do to do deserve this
- what did I do to make this happen 
- what did I do to deserve him

HELL NO! Someone who lies and cheats has absolutely NOTHING to do with you. That is their character not yours. “You think I’m dumb and naive but that’s you and not me, it’s time to face the truth.”
